AQA A-Level Psychology Specification (7181 / 7182)
For teaching from September 2025 | AS exams from June 2026 | A-level exams from June 2027

Assessment Structure
AS (7181) — 2 Papers, 144 marks total
Paper	Content	Time	Marks	Weighting
Paper 1: Introductory Topics	Social Influence, Memory, Attachment	1h 30m	72	50%
Paper 2: Psychology in Context	Approaches, Clinical Psychology & Mental Health, Research Methods	1h 30m	72	50%
Each paper: 3 sections × 24 marks. Question types: multiple choice, short answer, extended writing.

A-level (7182) — 3 Papers, 288 marks total
Paper	Content	Time	Marks	Weighting
Paper 1: Introductory Topics	Social Influence, Memory, Attachment, Clinical Psychology & Mental Health	2h	96	33.3%
Paper 2: Psychology in Context	Approaches, Biopsychology, Research Methods	2h	96	33.3%
